title: For Sale:  Saiga AK74 Bumpski 5.45x39
postcontent:
Selling my Converted Saiga Bumpski AK74 5.45x39. If you've ever wanted to shoot a full auto rifle but could never afford one of your own or get your hands on one to try out, here is your chance. First off, this rifle is "Not" an "Assault" rifle, it does "Not" shoot "Full-Auto", it "Simulates" full auto fire. It is a Bumpfire stock made by Fostech Outdoors. The Fostech Bumpski stock simulates full auto fire, with slight forward pressure using your forehand you will slide the gun forward engaging the trigger with your other hand, the recoil of the round being fired will reset the rifle and your continued forward pressure with your forehand will then engage the trigger again, simulating "Full-Auto" fire. There is only one shot for each trigger pull, therefore it is "Not" full auto. The rifle is very easy to use even for those that have never shot a bump fire stock. It is easy to control and empty a full magazine on target. The Bumpski Stock is made of aluminum, is adjustable from select fire mode to simulated full auto or Bumpfire mode,  and is adjustable for lefties or righties. This has been an extremely fun rifle to have, worth every penny because of the amount of joy myself and others got out of it. Everybody that has shot the rifle has had a smile from ear to ear. The rifle is in perfect condition and has less than 600 rounds through it. The rifle comes with a 1'' rubber recoil ruling butt pad, quick detach side rail scope mount, Magpul Angled fore grip, Tapco short vertical grip, tactical cammo soft carry case and (4) Tapco 30 rounds magazines. Asking $1,450.

title: For Sale:  STONER SR-15 CARBINE 5.56 MM NATO CALIBER
postcontent:
This is a limited edition, 1 of 1 package done by Hillbilly 223. The package includes a KAC SR-15,a custom, hand made dual action OTF auto knife , pelican case and mags all custom painted to match. This is an awesome package deal that will make all of your friends jealous. The pieces of this package will not be sold separately.

This item is in stock and ready to ship. Since it is in high demand and will sell fast, please email to inquire about availability. 


This item is new, we are a licensed gun shop and we received it from the manufacturer or a distributor. It has never been fired and since our shop specializes in more expensive, higher end merchandise we are not open to the public. This usually means you will get a pristine, mint condition example that has never been handled by anybody as most of our inventory is received and shipped out in the same box it arrived in and never even opened.

SR-15E3 IWS LPR
The KAC Light Precision Rifle (LPR) is the answer for 5.56mm shooters who want a light match system. The LPR utilizes an 18” Match Stainless Steel barrel with a Custom Match chamber, along with our IWS lower. Shooters will find that this weapon system offers a capable Competition System or Precision Perimeter Weapon for the Law Enforcement Sector.

E3 Enhanced Bolt
The E3 Enhanced Bolt from Knight’s Armament features a number of components designed to make this bolt the most durable and reliable bolt available. It is a proprietary bolt specifically designed for our SR15 and 16 models. The E3 Bolt boasts several features that add to the its overall performance such as the enlarged bolt face, rounded lugs, reduced cam pin, and proprietary extractor and firing pin designs.

This E3 Bolt is manufactured with an enlarged bolt face that provides more positive engagement in the chamber and lugs which are rounded to help to reduce chipping, cracking and snapping. This strengthened design helps to increase the life of the bolt and ensure a proper seating each time the weapon cycles.

The E3 Bolt’s extractor design is also a unique achievement that helps to provide an extremely reliable component. It’s shaped like a rounded ‘T’ and sometimes referred to as a ‘butterfly’ shape. The pivot point of the extractor is shifted forward to help balance out the extractor and apply constant pressure on the shell which reduces cases of extraction failures. Another strong feature of the unique design of this extractor is the use of two full size extractor springs, as opposed to the standard micro spring. This allows for a reduction of relative compression while the extractor is in motion and provides a failsafe in case one spring fails. The bolt will continue to function properly and afford a user the opportunity to continue with their mission or firing schedule.

The E3 Bolt is designed with a thinner Cam Pin and Firing Pin whose overall size has been reduced. The thinner Cam Pin allows for a thicker bolt web which is a common failure point in normal bolts. The reduction of the Firing Pin size is to accommodate the thinner Cam Pin.

The full capabilities of the E3 Bolt are realized when exposed to full auto or extremely high cyclic firing rates yet the bolt performs gracefully under casual firing conditions. This component was designed to be exposed to the most stressful and unrelenting conditions and exceed expectations for durability and service life

Ambidextrous Controls
Knight’s Armament designed this system to give shooters the maximum amount of options in their controls. Under this design all of the weapon’s major controls can be accessed from either side of the lower receiver. Left-handed shooters see the immediate benefits of being able to access the weapon’s controls in a more intuitive manner; however, there are a number of other benefits that right-handed shooters will enjoy under this system.

Competition shooters benefit from these controls from the increase of speed that is achieved through components such as the right-side bolt catch. Trainers enjoy the variety of options because they can watch their trainee from either side of the weapon and even manipulate the weapon’s controls from the non-operating side. KAC has also introduced modifications to the design such as the scalloped safety selector switch. This allows a lower profile for the selector switch on the non-operating side of the receiver which helps to relieve any interference between the switch and a shooter’s glove or hand. For the maximum amount of configuration and operation options, Knight’s Ambidextrous Controls offer a sure solution.

Two-Stage Match Trigger
All of the weapons available from Knight’s Armament come equipped with a 4.5lb, 2-Stage Match Trigger. This type of trigger mechanism uses a system where, during the rearward squeeze of a trigger, it cycles through two stages of resistance

The first stage is a ‘no-poundage’ stage where hardly any resistance is felt during the rear-ward squeeze. There is a center point at which point resistance is felt and the second stage of the trigger begins. At this point, 4.5 pounds of force is required to squeeze the trigger through the second stage and cause the weapon to cycle.

Our 2-stage trigger is meant to inform a shooter of exactly where their weapon is going to fire. This bolsters a firer’s confidence and can also assist in reducing trigger jerk, thereby increasing accuracy. The 4.5lb 2-Stage Trigger from Knight’s Armament is a highly calibrated and smooth component that is sure to be a welcome addition to any setup.


Universal Rail Extending (URX)
The evolution of the Universal Rail Extending (URX) begins over 20 years ago with Knight’s Armament pioneering the Modular Weapon System. Knight’s URX is a lightweight, free-floating, continuous top rail system that was designed to give a shooter the most diverse amount of placement options for any accessories they deemed helpful.

In an effort to relieve all weight, contact and stress from the barrel, the URX component was designed to be free-floating. This means that your barrel is not supporting or coming in contact with the rail system other than at the receiver. Under high firing rates, when the weapon’s barrel is heating up and undergoing greater amounts of stress, this system ensures accuracy is not affected by mounted accessories or a shooter’s manipulation of those accessories.

Several variations of the URX are available depending on your needs. They come in a variety of lengths, from our URX Carbine at 7” to our URX 3.1 7.62 at 14”. Knight’s latest systems are the URX 3.1 systems which feature a flat continuous top rail, several inches of mounting rails at the fore and rear ends of the sides and bottom, and slick sided portions in the middle sections. These slick sided portions provide a slimmer diameter for grip as well as an overall reduction in weight. Some of our other models, such as the URX II variations, include full length side and bottom rails and integrated front sights. These components provide the most amount of options with the least amount of interference.

title: For Sale:  Open bolt RPB M10, early gun, 3-digit SN with extras - semiauto MAC 10 in 9mm
postcontent:
This is a semi-auto version of the sub-gun commonly called the MAC-10.  Very early gun made by RPB, probably in 1978 (first year of production), given the low serial number.  If not, then it is a very early 1979 gun.  RPB used a "9" prefix on their serial numbers to denote 9mm in their early guns and the following numbers are sequential, so this is the 254th 9mm they made.  It comes with four of the very desirable Walther M10 steel mags and two Cobray Zytel magazines.  The Walthers hold 32 rounds and the Cobray hold 36, if I recall correctly.  The Walther mags command a high price - lowest you can usually find them is $100 each with some searching and patience, but they are more normally priced around $125-$150 retail.  The gun also comes with a factory shroud.  It is in very good condition overall, showing the rough machining and finish these are known for.  There are scattered marks and dings in the finish, as seen in the pics.  The shroud has some discoloration in the finish around some of the vent cuts, which I assume is related to heating of the metal during the cutting affecting the final color of the finish, as is is only around the cuts towards the rear.  Nice, early gun and not the easiest to find.  ATF banned manufacture of them in 1982 and subsequent guns had to be made with a closed bolt.  The existing open bolt guns, like this one, were grandfathered.

$1350 FIRM face to face in Hickory, NC.  The only trades I will consider are ones weighted heavily enough in my favor to be worth the extra time and effort of selling the trade goods.

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  1955/56 Russian SKS-45 Letter Gun
postcontent: For sale is a all matching as-issued Russian SKS-45 Letter Gun. This is more of a collectors rifle then a range gun. All serial's match on the bolt,dust cover,reciever,gastube-rod,stock,sight rail,buttplate and are correct for this late date/no factory stamp rifle. Bolt is in the white and the bayonet is gold colored with the blueing in great condition. There are a few handling marks on it which makes it as-issued instead of un-issued and the stock inspectors stamps are crisp and visible. The rifle has a backwards N that stands for the letter I in our alphabet and was used to year/date the rifle. The rifle was imported by KBI and has a smaller more desirable import stamp on the left side of the reciever after the star. postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=49

Item 4A (305gr. Hard Cast gas Checked LFN) is designed for super deep penetration on large game. The big flat nose keeps the bullet penetrating straight and thus deep. You can expect a good three + feet of penetration in normal flesh and bone. The flat nose also does considerably more damage than a round nosed type of bullet as the flat nose cuts and smashes it way through living matter, while round nosed bullets tend to slip and slide through matter, doing much less damage along the bullet’s path and achieving more shallow penetration due to getting sideways while “slipping and sliding” through matter.
You’ll note my below velocities from over-the-counter revolvers and rifles.

1.       Ruger Bisley cut down to 6 inches------1328 fps
2.       Ruger Red Hawk 5.5 inch-----------------1331 fps
3.       Marlin 1894 18.5 inch----------------------1779 fps
Item 4A is recommended for all STEEL revolvers and rifles on today’s market. It is not suitable for scandium or aluminum alloy revolvers.
